snippet.title: Johnny Depp sued "Aquaman- Amber Heard" for Libel to Demanding $ 50 million
snippet.description:
#JohnnyDepp #AmberHeard #JohnnyDeppAmberHeard #JohnnyDeppsuedAmberHeard

Hidden Radar

"Pirates of the Caribbean" sued Amber Heard for libel when he accused him of domestic violence, and asked beauty "Aquaman" to compensate $ 50 million.

Johnny Depp and Amber Heard's 2016 divorce is still interested in public opinion. Their relationship continues to be strained when Pirates of the Caribbean have filed a lawsuit against their ex-wife for libel, claiming up to $ 50 million.

According to The Blast, Depp describes Heard's alleged violence in the procession family as "a sophisticated hoax." “Mr. Depp never beat Heard. Her allegations are wrong. It was just part of a hoax to help Heard advance in his career, ”the lawsuit filed.

In this case, Depp also confirmed that the charge that Aquaman sent to the court earlier was dismissed by police because of third-party witnesses and 87 surveillance cameras as evidence.

And yet, according to The Blast, Depp said that his ex-wife was involved with technology billionaire Elon Musk when he and Heard had only been married for a month. This source said Pirates of the Caribbean have full evidence in this.
“Heard requested protection to allow‘ friend Elon ’into the parking lot and use the elevator at night to get to the building. Representative Depp then chased security agents out of court. They saw Elon leave this place the next morning, ”the source added.

Amber Heard's side still has no statement about the incident.
